
[1]forbearing

   FORBEARING, ppr.

   1. Ceasing; pausing; withholding from action; exercising patience and
   indulgence.

   2. a. Patient; long suffering.

     FORBEARING, n. A ceasing or restraining from action; patience; long
                                 suffering.
